1
00:00:32,958 --> 00:00:36,666
[HARUAKIRA] I trust you've
made progress, Kafet. Report.

2
00:00:36,750 --> 00:00:38,125
[KAFET]
Affirmative, Grand Master.

3
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:41,166
I brought the two of them here,
as you bade me.

4
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:42,833
The Drifters are both men.

5
00:00:42,916 --> 00:00:45,041
Quite advanced in
years to look at them.

6
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:47,208
And both at each
other's throats.

7
00:00:47,291 --> 00:00:50,041
What could I have done
to merit the hell of being

8
00:00:50,125 --> 00:00:52,625
marooned with this
thieving Roman?

9
00:00:52,708 --> 00:00:55,291
[SCIPIO grunts]
I didn'ta steal your tactics!

10
00:00:55,375 --> 00:00:57,000
I built upon your rude maneuver,

11
00:00:57,083 --> 00:00:59,875
thus refining it into
something new entirely!

12
00:00:59,958 --> 00:01:01,666
You're a thief!

13
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:03,000
You never would
have thought of that

14
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:05,375
two-front attack formation
you used at Zama,

15
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:08,208
if I hadn't crushed you with
it at Cannae, you dog!

16
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:11,000
History will remember
me as a tactical genius!

17
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:12,708
To the victor goes the spoils!

18
00:01:12,791 --> 00:01:14,750
Oh, really? I don't
seem to recall you

19
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,750
crossing the Alps
on an elephant!

20
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:19,458
That damnable gimmick is
all you ever go on about!

21
00:01:19,541 --> 00:01:21,750
[BOTH grunting]

22
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,208
[HANNIBAL] If I had an
elephant right now,

23
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:24,291
I'd show you a gimmick!

24
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:25,291
[SCIPIO]
When I get back,

25
00:01:25,375 --> 00:01:26,750
I'll salt your
precious Carthage!

26
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:27,958
[HANNIBAL]
When I get back,

27
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:31,875
I'll sack Rome and
piss in the Tiber!

28
00:01:31,958 --> 00:01:34,833
[KAFET] What would you have
me do next, Grand Master?

29
00:01:34,916 --> 00:01:37,583
[HARUAKIRA]
Stop them.

30
00:01:37,666 --> 00:01:39,916
Yes, sir. As you wish.

31
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,500
[HARUAKIRA]
These Drifters are as powerful

32
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:46,541
as they are enigmatic.

33
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:49,250
We don't know what
they aim to do.

34
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,708
We must learn of
their intentions.

35
00:01:51,791 --> 00:01:53,875
Fail at this task,

36
00:01:53,958 --> 00:01:56,875
and the world we know
will be annihilated.

37
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:39,000
[SHARA speaking Orte]


38
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:51,791
[speaking Orte]


39
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:56,833
[SHARA speaking Orte]


40
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:08,583
[speaking Orte]


41
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:13,625
[NOBUNAGA, TOYOHISA snoring]

42
00:04:17,375 --> 00:04:19,375
So, you noticed, too?

43
00:04:19,458 --> 00:04:22,000
[TOYOHISA]
I smell it,

44
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:24,250
but I can't make it out.

45
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:26,916
There's carnage
in the air tonight.

46
00:04:29,041 --> 00:04:30,958
[grunts]

47
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:36,833
Something's burning. I'd wager
it's the nearby village.

48
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:40,208
Bandits must have
set fire to the place.

49
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:43,916
The Elves are under attack.
That's what you're smelling.

50
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,208
[TOYOHISA]
What are "Elves"?

51
00:04:45,291 --> 00:04:46,500
They're an odd little folk

52
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:48,958
who live beyond the
edge of the forest.

53
00:04:49,041 --> 00:04:50,500
As it turns out,

54
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:53,583
it was two of them who dragged
you here as you were dying.

55
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:55,541
[NOBUNAGA]
Hey!

56
00:04:55,625 --> 00:04:58,083
Dammit, Toyohisa!
What are you doing?

57
00:04:58,166 --> 00:05:00,791
I don't know what this
place is, or how I got here!

58
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:03,333
Maybe this is a fever-dream,
or maybe I'm a corpse!

59
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:07,500
But, alive or dead,
Shimazu Toyohisa can fight!

60
00:05:11,125 --> 00:05:13,291
And he's off,
running into trouble.

61
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:16,708
Never mind the fact you just
stitched him back together.

62
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:18,708
He's got the temperament
of a musket ball.

63
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:19,958
[YOICHI chuckles]

64
00:05:21,166 --> 00:05:23,000
[chuckles]

65
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:25,833
[OLMINU] Does this
mean they're mobilizing?

66
00:05:25,916 --> 00:05:27,416
[NOBUNAGA]
Onward!

67
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:30,166
Look at them go!
What do they mean to do?

68
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:34,208
[gasps]

69
00:05:36,208 --> 00:05:37,750
[TOYOHISA] Good of you
to join us, Nobunaga!

70
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:39,291
Should we slow down?

71
00:05:39,375 --> 00:05:40,958
I thought the Demon
King of the Sixth

72
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,166
Heaven would be
lighter on his feet!

73
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:47,083
Bastard! We'll see how fast you
run when you're pushing fifty!

74
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:49,916
And how old are you,
Lord Toyohisa?

75
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,500
Thirty, you?

76
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:55,250
[chuckles]

77
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:56,583
What're you laughin' about?

78
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,291
I'm still in the
bloom of youth, imp!

79
00:05:58,375 --> 00:06:02,458
The histories left out the part
where Yoichi was a huge dick!

80
00:06:05,958 --> 00:06:06,708
[gasps]

81
00:06:06,791 --> 00:06:10,083
[BOTH panting]

82
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:14,041
[speaking Orte]


83
00:06:14,125 --> 00:06:15,541
[whimpers]

84
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:18,750
[BOTH panting]

85
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:19,833
[gasps]

86
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:27,750
[ORTE SOLDIERS gasp]

87
00:06:30,916 --> 00:06:33,416
[TOYOHISA]
So, yeah. I'm feeling better.

88
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:43,000
[yelling, grunting]

89
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:49,250
I'm gonna cut your
head clean off!

90
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:54,166
[speaking Orte]


91
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,291
Your words don't make any sense.

92
00:06:56,375 --> 00:06:59,291
I have no idea what the hell
you're trying to say to me.

93
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:01,333
Tell me again in my language!

94
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:03,750
[grunting]

95
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:06,875
[TOYOHISA] Addressing me in a
foreign tongue is an insult!

96
00:07:06,958 --> 00:07:08,250
A mortal one!

97
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,291
[grunts]

98
00:07:12,416 --> 00:07:14,583
[screams]

99
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:17,916
[TOYOHISA growls]

100
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:20,791
[BOTH whimper]

101
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:23,666
Heh! Yeah, you two
are odd little folk.

102
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:27,208
[whimpering continues]

103
00:07:27,291 --> 00:07:29,166
[TOYOHISA] If you hadn't
dragged me to my countrymen,

104
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,458
I'd be dead.

105
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:33,583
Saving your lives was
the least I could do!

106
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:35,083
[MASHA gasps]

107
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:37,875
Well, you seem to have
adopted a softer tone.

108
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:38,750
[TOYOHISA]
Huh?

109
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:39,833
You just killed
that soldier

110
00:07:39,916 --> 00:07:41,875
for the sin of not
speaking like us.

111
00:07:41,958 --> 00:07:44,166
Quite hypocritical,
don't you think?

112
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:47,041
[TOYOHISA growls]

113
00:07:47,125 --> 00:07:48,333
Repeat the following!

114
00:07:48,416 --> 00:07:51,375
"Help me, Toyohisa!
You're my only hope!"

115
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:52,125
[MASHA, MARK]
Huh?

116
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:53,291
Say the damn words!

117
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:55,291
"Help me, Toyohisa!"
"Help me, Toyohisa!"

118
00:07:55,375 --> 00:07:58,958
[BOTH] "Help me, Toyohisa!"
"Help me, Toyohisa!"

119
00:07:59,041 --> 00:08:00,791
There, ya see?

120
00:08:00,875 --> 00:08:02,916
That wasn't so hard, was it?

121
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,041
Please do not poke fun
at him like that again.

122
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:06,250
And the worst part is,

123
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:09,291
you can tell he's so
damn proud of himself.

124
00:08:16,541 --> 00:08:19,041
[NOBUNAGA] Barring heads,
they're all well-equipped.

125
00:08:19,125 --> 00:08:22,375
No raggedy band of
half-armored raiders, this.

126
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:24,208
Actual soldiers.

127
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:26,708
The lord's forces, perhaps?

128
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:28,833
[NOBUNAGA]
Amateurs.

129
00:08:28,916 --> 00:08:32,625
It's like they're asking me
to seize their domain.

130
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:40,250
[NOBUNAGA]
I've made my decision, you two.

131
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:43,208
It's time for us to
take the village.

132
00:08:43,291 --> 00:08:45,958
[HARUAKIRA] Hold on.
Did he say "take"?

133
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:47,208
[OLMINU]
Yes.

134
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:48,541
[HARUAKIRA]
He could have said

135
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:52,041
"retake," or "reclaim,"
or "take back," but no...

136
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:54,416
It's a part of their nature,
down to the bones.

137
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,666
Their fatal flaw, and their
greatest strength.

138
00:08:57,750 --> 00:09:01,041
Rather, It is the only
strength they possess.

139
00:09:01,125 --> 00:09:03,000
No matter his place in history,

140
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:08,208
man has one animus that
guides him. One urge, above all.

141
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:11,833
He desires conquest,
for good or ill.

142
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:17,166
[ARAM speaking Orte]


143
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:21,375
[ELFS grunting]

144
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:28,791
[speaking Orte]


145
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:36,250
[speaking Orte]


146
00:09:38,166 --> 00:09:39,458
[gasps]

147
00:09:39,541 --> 00:09:44,500
[speaking Orte]


148
00:09:48,666 --> 00:09:53,708
[speaking Orte]


149
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:58,750
[speaking Orte]


150
00:10:14,708 --> 00:10:19,666
[speaking Orte]


151
00:10:36,583 --> 00:10:41,541
[speaking Orte]


152
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:57,125
[groans]

153
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:06,791
[speaking Orte]


154
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,416
[screams]

155
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:20,500
[speaking Orte]


156
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,916
[growls]

157
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:43,333
[speaking Orte]


158
00:11:43,416 --> 00:11:44,958
[SHARA grunts]

159
00:11:45,041 --> 00:11:47,458
[ORTE SOLDIER F speaking Orte]


160
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:49,041
[ARAM speaking Orte]


161
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:54,083
[speaking Orte]


162
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:07,833
Why did you burn their wheat?

163
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:11,125
[NOBUNAGA] Simple. A man can
endure the loss of dignity,

164
00:12:11,208 --> 00:12:13,750
so long as his hunger's met.

165
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,208
And on the other hand,

166
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:18,291
hunger is nothing to a
man who has dignity.

167
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:19,916
When you take away both,

168
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,291
when they're scared and
have nothing to lose,

169
00:12:22,375 --> 00:12:25,375
that's when people rise up.

170
00:12:25,458 --> 00:12:26,916
Those rabble-rousing monks

171
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,875
used this trick against
me back in the day.

172
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,041
It's a good way
to steal a country

173
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:33,458
out from under someone.

174
00:12:33,541 --> 00:12:36,458
[chuckles]
Aren't you a frightening one?

175
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:42,875
Oh, but those bastards
got what they deserved.

176
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:46,333
Burned every last
one at Nagashima.

177
00:12:46,416 --> 00:12:51,375
[NOBUNAGA laughs]

178
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:03,291
[speaking Orte]


179
00:13:16,416 --> 00:13:17,416
[ARAM gasps]

180
00:13:19,375 --> 00:13:20,916
[speaking Orte]


181
00:13:30,166 --> 00:13:31,041
[TOYOHISA]
One!

182
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:32,416
[ARAM speaking ORTE]


183
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:35,750
[ALL gasp]

184
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:40,791
[ARAM speaking ORTE]


185
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:47,791
[TOYOHISA grunts]

186
00:13:47,875 --> 00:13:49,750
[TOYOHISA]
Two!

187
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:51,916
[ORTE SOLDIERS grunt]

188
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,041
[TOYOHISA]
Three!

189
00:13:53,125 --> 00:13:55,041
[ORTE SOLDIERS gasp]

190
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:57,041
[speaking ORTE]


191
00:13:57,125 --> 00:14:00,708
[grunting]

192
00:14:00,791 --> 00:14:01,916
[TOYOHISA]
Four!

193
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:05,000
[ALL gasp]

194
00:14:09,541 --> 00:14:12,166
You there, in the cape.

195
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:14,833
You've a good head
on your shoulders.

196
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,416
A commander's head.

197
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:22,333
How 'bout... you leave it
here for my collection?

198
00:14:22,416 --> 00:14:27,375
[speaking Orte]


199
00:14:33,416 --> 00:14:34,583
[MASHA speaking Orte]


200
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:35,250
[gasps]

201
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:37,291
[BOTH speaking Orte]


202
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:42,333
[speaking Orte]


203
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:48,041
[MARK speaking Orte]


204
00:14:48,125 --> 00:14:53,083
[speaking Orte]

205
00:14:59,125 --> 00:15:00,250
[TOYOHISA grunts]

206
00:15:02,125 --> 00:15:04,250
[ELF FATHER sobs]

207
00:15:08,375 --> 00:15:11,416
[growls]
How dare you?

208
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:14,166
How dare you slaughter
the unarmed?

209
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:15,583
[chuckles]

210
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:19,583
[TOYOHISA] I don't
want your head anymore.

211
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:22,208
I wanna send your soul to hell!

212
00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:27,291
[speaking Orte]


213
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:40,208
[speaking Orte]


214
00:15:44,916 --> 00:15:50,125
[TOYOHISA grunts]

215
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:54,250
[speaking Orte]


216
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:55,458
[gasps]

217
00:15:56,916 --> 00:16:01,958
[BOTH grunting]

218
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:05,083
Down... you... go!

219
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:11,041
[grunting]

220
00:16:11,125 --> 00:16:13,791
Too easy! Waste of my time!

221
00:16:13,875 --> 00:16:15,541
[whimpers]

222
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:19,416
[speaking Orte]


223
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:21,166
[grunts]

224
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:26,000
[ARAM whimpers]

225
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:34,000
[ARAM grunts, shouts]

226
00:16:34,416 --> 00:16:36,333
[ALL gasping]

227
00:16:36,416 --> 00:16:40,583
[ARAM gurgles]

228
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:43,833
[ALL gasping]

229
00:16:43,916 --> 00:16:45,958
[NOBUNAGA] The boy
knows how to fight.

230
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:50,875
Using his scabbard in lieu
of a sword? Such brutality!

231
00:16:50,958 --> 00:16:51,958
[gasps]

232
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:55,333
What a sight!
Glad he's on our side.

233
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:57,416
Have you finished your task?

234
00:16:57,500 --> 00:17:03,708
Indeed. His minions fled in
the dark, but I found them.

235
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:05,750
Toyohisa may scare his foe,

236
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,875
but your foe never
sees you coming.

237
00:17:10,416 --> 00:17:11,791
[NOBUNAGA]
All right, then.

238
00:17:11,875 --> 00:17:14,208
How's this puppet
show gonna end?

239
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:19,250
[ARAM continues grunting]

240
00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:21,916
--[TOYOHISA grunts]
--[neck crackles]

241
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,958
[speaking Orte]


242
00:17:27,291 --> 00:17:29,583
[ELVES gasp]

243
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:37,833
[sobs]

244
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:40,375
[TOYOHISA exhales]

245
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:46,250
[ELVES gasping]

246
00:17:50,916 --> 00:17:52,416
[gasps]

247
00:17:54,375 --> 00:17:55,208
[TOYOHISA]
Take it.

248
00:17:55,291 --> 00:17:58,625
[ELF FATHER gasps]

249
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:04,000
[TOYOHISA]
End his life.

250
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,625
[whimpers]

251
00:18:05,708 --> 00:18:07,958
He has to die! By your hand! 

252
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:11,000
Pick up that sword and sheathe
it in that villain's heart!

253
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:12,416
I don't know a
thing about you,

254
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:14,333
whether you were a
good father or bad!

255
00:18:14,416 --> 00:18:17,208
All I know is your son
lies dead at your feet!

256
00:18:17,291 --> 00:18:20,250
You couldn't save his life,
but you can avenge it!

257
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:22,333
[ELVES gasp]

258
00:18:22,416 --> 00:18:24,208
[NOBUNAGA] His words
remain a riddle to them,

259
00:18:24,291 --> 00:18:28,041
but when it comes to his intent,
no way can they plead ignorance.

260
00:18:28,125 --> 00:18:31,666
[chuckles]
Quite a man, that one.

261
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:36,708
[ELF FATHER whimpers]

262
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:55,250
[ARAM groans]

263
00:18:57,708 --> 00:19:02,666
[speaking Orte]


264
00:19:10,541 --> 00:19:16,083
[ARAM yells]

265
00:19:24,541 --> 00:19:28,750
[ELF FATHER sobs]

266
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:35,291
For your son.

267
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:37,833
Good work.

268
00:19:37,916 --> 00:19:39,875
'Sup!

269
00:19:39,958 --> 00:19:41,625
Where the hell were
you durin' all that?

270
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:43,500
I still got thread
holdin' me together!

271
00:19:43,583 --> 00:19:45,708
We were busy, doin' stuff.

272
00:19:45,791 --> 00:19:47,166
Busy! What he said!

273
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:48,666
Bet you're beat!

274
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:51,458
Please, make yourself comfy
on this nearby wooden crate!

275
00:19:51,541 --> 00:19:53,541
Take a load off,
Toyohisa, my man.

276
00:19:53,625 --> 00:19:56,958
You've earned it,
with your heroics tonight.

277
00:19:57,041 --> 00:19:58,375
[TOYOHISA grunts]

278
00:19:58,458 --> 00:19:59,458
[OLMINU]
I can't believe it!

279
00:19:59,541 --> 00:20:02,041
I'm seeing it,
but how's it possible?

280
00:20:02,125 --> 00:20:05,541
The three Drifters took on a
knight and his foot soldiers...

281
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:07,500
...and killed the bunch!

282
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:19,375
[TOYOHISA]
Hmph.

283
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:26,833
[MURASAKI]
Hm.

284
00:20:26,916 --> 00:20:31,875
[MALE VOICE chants]

285
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:37,541
[EASY] Look at you
with your little desk.

286
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:40,416
Quite the heroic figure
you're cutting there.

287
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:43,208
Push that boulder for as
long as you like, Murasaki.

288
00:20:43,291 --> 00:20:47,375
You can throw the best possible
examples of humanity into play.

289
00:20:47,458 --> 00:20:50,458
When all's said and done,
I'll be the winner.

290
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:55,000
Pardon my French,
but you're pissing in the wind.

291
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:57,875
Deep down, I think you
know that I'm right.

292
00:20:57,958 --> 00:20:59,250
[MURASAKI]
Get out of here, EASY.

293
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:02,125
Their are wrongs
that must be righted

294
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:03,625
[EASY grunts]

295
00:21:05,916 --> 00:21:09,916
Go ahead, scowl at me. But I am
not letting you have your way.

296
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,333
[gasps]

297
00:21:12,416 --> 00:21:14,541
[MURASAKI]
Leave this place, wretch.

298
00:21:14,625 --> 00:21:15,750
[growls]

299
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:18,250
You're quick with the
big talk, Murasaki.

300
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,958
If you think you can
outmaneuver me,

301
00:21:20,041 --> 00:21:21,708
go ahead and try!

302
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:25,916
[MURASAKI gasps]

303
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:28,458
My Ends are gonna
massacre your Drifters.

304
00:21:28,541 --> 00:21:33,000
I so look forward to showing you
your heroes' heads on pikes!

305
00:21:35,291 --> 00:21:37,708
[OLMINU] This is Olmine!
Repeat, this is Olmine!

306
00:21:37,791 --> 00:21:39,458
Grand Master,
the trio of Drifters

307
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:41,333
just claimed the
village of Elves!

308
00:21:41,416 --> 00:21:43,500
It's dangerous to
let them run riot!

309
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:45,500
Give me the order to
bring them in, sir!

310
00:21:45,583 --> 00:21:47,750
Negative, Olmine.
There's no time for that.

311
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:51,041
Do not bring them here.
Keep your distance.

312
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:53,500
[OLMINU]
What? You... you mean?

313
00:21:53,583 --> 00:21:56,333
That's right. The die is cast.

314
00:22:07,708 --> 00:22:10,041
The battle is about to begin!

315
00:23:56,541 --> 00:24:01,500
[MALE VOICE chants]

